# Pi extensions (short)

For **how agent memory works** (sessions, recaps, `/remember`), read **[docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md](docs/AGENT_MEMORY.md)**. For **memory vs tools vs specs**, read **[docs/SYSTEM.md](docs/SYSTEM.md)**. For **tools** vs **skills** vs **agents** vs **extensions**, read **[docs/CONCEPTS.md](docs/CONCEPTS.md)** and as needed **[docs/TOOLS.md](docs/TOOLS.md)**, **[docs/SKILLS.md](docs/SKILLS.md)**, **[docs/AGENTS.md](docs/AGENTS.md)**, **[docs/AGENT_TEAMS.md](docs/AGENT_TEAMS.md)**. When you add or change **Pi** behavior (TUI, slash commands, hooks, tools), read **[docs/EXTENSIONS.md](docs/EXTENSIONS.md)**. Implement under **`extensions/`**; add a one-line re-export under **`.pi/extensions/`** and list it in **`.pi/settings.json`** — never put **`themeMap.ts`** or non-extensions in **`.pi/extensions/`**. After edits, the user should run **`/reload`** in Pi. Full checklist and upstream links are in the doc.
